node.text: brother @dreanthraxghoul. camagu, injalo. my heart is warm thinking of you. thank you for these words + for deepening/widening my understanding of what it is to heal. i will see you very very soon, mkhulu. and, i love you

..
R A P E
.
.
it's chilling to learn of just how many woman have been sexually assaulted. womxn close to me. and womxn across the world.
.
.
i am one of them. .
.
it pains me to think of the countless numbers of boys and men who have been violated in this way.
.
.
rape, against anyone, is unjust. .
.
the other day I read something someone wrote and it said: 'rape is worse than death'. that struck me and it got me thinking more deeply about rape and the effects it has on ones soul, psyche, sense of self worth, consciousness and the lens through which we view the world.
.
.
i have the very precious assignment of being conduit and space holder for the beings who sit across from me in the sacred contract of finding healing together. its an honour and blessing. for a long time, this responsibility scared me (it still does), and i held back because something about it felt too big, and I questioned whether i really was the person for the job and whether i had the capacity to handle another's heart. .
.
i don't know how many times i have broken. i broke many times as i young adult, though i didnt know that this is in fact what i was experiencing. i numbed myself in various ways and only understood and acknowledged what i was doing many years in. i self sabbotaged. i poisoned myself with unhealthy foods, alcohol, negative self talk, and by betraying myself by allowing others to betray and subjugate me. by accepting what i didnt deserve and in not keeping the promises i made to myself. 
i've lost count of the number of times i've broken my own heart. .
.
my reflections over the past few weeks, are showing me three things as it becomes obvious that what is being communicated is more than mere thoughts. 
one - this is coming back up to the surface because i have not completely dealt with and healed from my own trauma. i accept that this journey my never leave me entirely, but my perspective is continously changing and easing. 
two - im being guided towards one of the focuses of my practice and being shown where our healing is needed. .
.
(continued in comments)

i truly accept that we have the experiences we have so we can use them as medicine to soothe those whove experienced something similar. i bless every painful or teaumatic experience because i know how to sit in the fire with someone else and bot shrink back, and not want to hide or break down. i can hold space in love and optimism because i know that all journeys are meant for us and are there to teach us something, if we will be brave enough to ask to be shown what is on the other side. 
three - we have a big problem. a crisis. and we need to look at the places in the dark, that are causing this phenomena in our communities. broken people break people. unless we get to healing this part, our society will only coninue to decay. there's a bigger problem behind the problem. the souls of the world has been fondled foe centuries ans we need to talk about it all. 
im writing this post because words are medicine, and because our stories can be the cure. i write this post to salute you if you are a survivor of rape. iam so so sorry that it happened to you. you did not deserve it. it wasnt your fault. your vouce and your story us valid. 
i send love to you if you've felt the pain and emptiness of trying to love anyone who experienced this back to life and fought to convince them that they are seen, that they are beautyful, that they are worthy, and that they are enough. that life is worth living. 
if you've been the perpetrator, i hold you in compassion and i pray that you'll find your own healing and that you'll find the courage and honesty to confront all of the stuff that led you to that place. i am sorry for our scars. i am sorry any of us got here. 
in courage i send you love. we are all in this together. we have to take care of this precious responsibility, and it starts with tending our own gardens. once we take accountability for our experiences and are truthful with it all, whatever it is, we can truly begin to heal.

brother @dreanthraxghoul. camagu, injalo. my heart is warm thinking of you. thank you for these words + for deepening/widening my understanding of what it is to heal. i will see you very very soon, mkhulu. and, i love you

✊🏽Healing is analysis and understanding. Healing is expanding space. Healing is art. Healing is simple. Healing is the power of loving and treasuring yourself that you take to negate the power of violence, of the tormented mind. You are free indeed Vuyo. You have healed yourself and now you are so expansive in love, in expanding the power of love to help others heal.
thank you for your words @rudy_madamefluff. recieved with love 🌻🖤
Thank you 🙏🏾 You have been sent to this earth to do a very special job, I salute you for your grace and compassion. This post hit home, as I’m sure it did for many others ❤️
We honour you work Gogo. Camagu.
